@startuml sequence_technician_assignment
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Work Order Technician Assignment — Identity Fix

actor User
participant "WorkOrdersComponent" as WO
participant "REST API" as API
database "SQL Server" as DB

== Load Technicians (ngOnInit) ==
User -> WO: Open create work order
WO -> API: GET /users
API -> DB: SELECT Id, DisplayName, Role, IsActive\nFROM Users\nWHERE OrgId = @OrgId
DB --> API: users[]
API --> WO: users[]
WO -> WO: Filter: isActive &&\nrole in ['Technician','FleetManager']
WO -> WO: Map to { id: GUID, displayName }

== Select Technician ==
User -> WO: Click assignee dropdown
WO --> User: Show filtered technicians\n(real names from API)
User -> WO: Select technician
WO -> WO: newWorkOrder.assignedTo =\n{ id: "3fa85f64-...", displayName: "Alex Chen" }

== Create Work Order ==
User -> WO: Click Submit
WO -> API: POST /work-orders\n{\n  equipmentId: "...",\n  serviceType: "Corrective",\n  priority: "High",\n  description: "...",\n  assignedToUserId: "3fa85f64-..."\n}
note right of API: assignedToUserId is a\nvalid user GUID, NOT\na string name like\n"John Smith"
API -> DB: INSERT WorkOrder\nSET AssignedToUserId = @UserId
DB --> API: created workOrder
API --> WO: workOrder (with AssignedTo nav property)
WO --> User: Show in list with\ntechnician display name

== Unassigned Case ==
User -> WO: Submit without selecting technician
WO -> API: POST /work-orders\n{ ..., assignedToUserId: null }
API -> DB: INSERT WorkOrder\nSET AssignedToUserId = NULL
DB --> API: created workOrder
API --> WO: workOrder
WO --> User: Shows "Unassigned"

@enduml
